column5: Not sure if this has been posted before.  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_VKouBHarIo&feature=related
Thanks me Brudder. Sounds decent...a cross between Bob Dylan and Warren Zevon.
Would you call that a fiddle or violin there? No matter,it,s a nice touch to the song.East coast flavor, even though the the band  includes members from Scotlandï»¿, Ireland, England and the USA .

Man, I still have that album (vinyl) + on my MP3 player...love that song, great band that came out of Ireland just after U2 waaaaaaay back in the early 80's.  They released a really wicked album in 1984 called A Pagan Place...good stuff!

I just came across this band by mistake. Been listen to them all night.Great band.
